<section class="section_container" id="venue">
  <div class="flex_center">
    <%= image_tag("three_trees.png", id: "three_trees") %>
  </div>

  <header>
    <h2 class="section_header">Venue</h2>
  </header>
  <div class="section group">
    <div class="col span_1_of_2">
      <p>
        <%= link_to("Wellspring Spa", "http://wellspringspa.com/") %> sits just outside Mt. Rainier National Park. It is a wonderful and somewhat remote space that highlights the beauty of Washington's forests. 
      </p>
      <p>
        Here are some things to know about where we’ll be saying “I do:”
      </p>
      <p>
        There are woodland trails around the entire property. The trails are dirt and have roots and rocks that stick up. There isn’t much elevation gain across the property but there is a ⅓ mile “hike” from the Gazebo, the site of the pre-ceremony drinks, to the Sanctuary, where the ceremony will take place. We will also be having the reception on a lawn. Please plan ahead when choosing your footwear! 
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col span_1_of_2">
      <p>
        As with any location in Washington, there is always the chance of rain. Also, being out in the woods means it most likely will cool off in the evening (mid 40s). We suggest coming prepared with several layers to change into. 
      </p>
      <p>
        Wellspring Spa is remote. There is <span class="emphasis">very limited, to no cell coverage</span>. Do not plan on having access to your devices while at the property (or in Mt. Rainier National Park). There is a landline phone booth in Ashford if you need to place a call. 
      </p>
      <p>
        <span class="emphasis">No pets</span> and <span class="emphasis">no smoking</span> will be allowed on the property, and fires are only allowed in the designated ring in the Gazebo. Please help us maintain the beauty of the location by following a “leave no trace” policy. 
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

